E. COLI 0157 - JAPAN (3): BACKGROUND
====================================
Date: Sun, 16 Jun 1996 06:11:11 +0300 (IDT)
From: "Prof. Berger" <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

>From the GIDEON software:

68 sporadic and 79 outbreak-associated cases of VTEC enterohemorrhagic _E.
coli_ reported in Japan during January 1992 to July 1993.
VTEC peaks during July to August in this country - 52% of cases are ages 6
to 15.

6,783 isolates of enteropathogenic _E. coli_ recovered during 1991 through
1995 (351 of these VTEC).
29 cases of hemolytic uremic syndrome associated with VTEC were reported
during 1991 to 1994.
No data on the current outbreak.
....................................................................JW


